{"questionId":"6036","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A cylinder is fitted with a piston. A fixed mass of an ideal gas fills the space above the piston.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"https://ib-questionbank-attachments.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/tinymce_asset/asset/4756/Schermafbeelding_2018-08-12_om_16.52.30.png\" alt=\"M18/4/PHYSI/SP3/ENG/TZ2/07._01\"></p>\n<p>The gas expands isobarically. The following data are available.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><span class=\"mjpage mjpage__block\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"block\" alttext=\"\\begin{array}{*{20}{l}} {{\\text{Amount of gas}}}&amp;{ = 243{\\text{ mol}}} \\\\ {{\\text{Initial volume of gas}}}&amp;{ = 47.1{\\text{ }}{{\\text{m}}^3}} \\\\ {{\\text{Initial temperature of gas}}}&amp;{ = -12.0{\\text{ °C}}} \\\\ {{\\text{Final temperature of gas}}}&amp;{ = + 19.0{\\text{ °C}}} \\\\ {{\\text{Initial pressure of gas}}}&amp;{ = 11.2{\\text{ kPa}}} \\end{array}\">\n  <mtable columnalign=\"left\" rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n    <mtr>\n      <mtd>\n        <mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>Amount of gas</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n      </mtd>\n      <mtd>\n        <mrow>\n          <mo>=</mo>\n          <mn>243</mn>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>&nbsp;mol</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n      </mtd>\n    </mtr>\n    <mtr>\n      <mtd>\n        <mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>Initial volume of gas</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n      </mtd>\n      <mtd>\n        <mrow>\n          <mo>=</mo>\n          <mn>47.1</mn>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>&nbsp;</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <msup>\n              <mrow>\n                <mtext>m</mtext>\n              </mrow>\n              <mn>3</mn>\n            </msup>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n      </mtd>\n    </mtr>\n    <mtr>\n      <mtd>\n        <mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>Initial temperature of gas</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n      </mtd>\n      <mtd>\n        <mrow>\n          <mo>=</mo>\n          <mo>−</mo>\n          <mn>12.0</mn>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>&nbsp;°C</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n      </mtd>\n    </mtr>\n    <mtr>\n      <mtd>\n        <mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>Final temperature of gas</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n      </mtd>\n      <mtd>\n        <mrow>\n          <mo>=</mo>\n          <mo>+</mo>\n          <mn>19.0</mn>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>&nbsp;°C</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n      </mtd>\n    </mtr>\n    <mtr>\n      <mtd>\n        <mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>Initial pressure of gas</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n      </mtd>\n      <mtd>\n        <mrow>\n          <mo>=</mo>\n          <mn>11.2</mn>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>&nbsp;kPa</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n      </mtd>\n    </mtr>\n  </mtable>\n</math></span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The gas returns to its original state by an adiabatic compression followed by cooling at&nbsp;constant volume.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Sketch, on the <em>pV </em>diagram, the complete cycle of changes for the gas,&nbsp;labelling the changes clearly. The expansion shown in (a) and (b) is drawn&nbsp;for you.</p>\n<p><img src=\"__IMG__/35c59fb0400914d0a1094b2681f3e5a466110781.png\"></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>concave curve from RHS of present line to point above LHS of present line</p>\n<p>vertical line from previous curve to the beginning</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://ib-questionbank-attachments.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/tinymce_asset/asset/4769/Schermafbeelding_2018-08-13_om_08.30.16.png\" alt=\"M18/4/PHYSI/SP3/ENG/TZ2/07.d.i/M\"></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"6036","referenceCode":"18M.3.SL.TZ2.7d.i","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Sketch, on the pV diagram, the complete cycle of changes for the gas, labelling the changes clearly. The expansion shown in (a) and (b) is drawn for you.","paper":"3","level":"SL","questionNumber":"d.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Option B: Engineering physics","Option B: Engineering physics","Option B: Engineering physics (Core topics)","B.2 – Thermodynamics","Option B: Engineering physics","Option B: Engineering physics (Core topics)"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}